Pre-Game Insights: The Canadian men’s national team will face France, the second-best national team in the world as of the latest FIFA rankings, on June 9, 2024.
This match will be just the second game for Canada under coach Jesse Marsch and their last before they take on Argentina at the Copa América.
France coach Didier Deschamps will use this match as his final chance to evaluate his team before Euro 2024.
Kylian Mbappé's recent move from Paris Saint-Germain to Real Madrid was announced this week, adding to the anticipation of his performance in the match.
France's squad includes players from Europe's top five leagues, with many having won titles with clubs like Real Madrid, PSG, and Inter Milan.
Canadian players like Tajon Buchanan and Alphonso Davies will face familiar opponents from their club teams.
Miscellaneous Highlights: France's recent form includes a 3-0 win over Luxembourg and a 2-0 loss to Germany in friendlies, as well as a 3-2 win over Chile.
France qualified for Euro 2024 by topping their group with a 7-1-0 record, including a 4-0 victory over the Netherlands.
